    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="867"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d867">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/400.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 29, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your June 25. Receivership can not enter into full operation until terms of
                    settlement are approved by bankers and the bonds definitely issued. It is
                    recommended that the receivership be established in form on July 1. Receivership
                    could be constituted and given all functions provided in the contract not
                    inconsistent with the collection of revenue under the present Erlanger
                    agreement, provided that on withdrawal of the collectors appointed under
                    Erlanger agreement the customs receivership should enter into all of the
                    functions provided by the contract.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
